<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb6a4d687-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300ff–136"><num value="300ff–136">§ 300ff–136.</num><heading> Selection of designated officers</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb6a4d688-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300ff–136/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of receiving notifications and responses and making requests under this part on behalf of emergency response employees, the public health officer of each State shall designate 1 official or officer of each employer of emergency response employees in the State.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb6a4d689-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300ff–136/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Preference in making designations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In making the designations required in subsection (a), a public health officer shall give preference to individuals who are trained in the provision of health care or in the control of infectious diseases.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idb6a4d68a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title XXVI, § 2695E, as added <ref href="/us/pl/111/87/s13">Pub. L. 111–87, § 13</ref>, <date date="2009-10-30">Oct. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/2901">123 Stat. 2901</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
